<subSubSection id="272120A7A45D6BB8D52916BEB58354D6" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="description">
<paragraph id="71B4901CB7B2FCB464892CB9C1653254" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Diagnostic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C514B78F94B5829F8A324DE35C076DA2" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Entirely dark brown to black, except by paired pink vittae on pronotal disc (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5694735151CA3BCD022EDF7349536C22" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16A</figureCitation>
), as about as long as 1/2
<normalizedToken id="E864EEDF7367FEC84EFD5FE21850A965" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
disc length, as wide as 1/3
<normalizedToken id="7D7F6EE7AF0E24DE99A4CBD32379EF9D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
disc width. Elytron (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CAAF3D6DF5A8793A48830AEAA22B135E" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16A</figureCitation>
) dark brown to black, without any pale-yellow longitudinal stripe. Legs (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E223035AA198AD071DFAA3F00D4D0C28" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16B</figureCitation>
) dark brown to black. Sternum VIII entirely dark brown, without lateral vitreous spots. Pygidium (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6AE2FD1E19F868C469D335419BBAD834" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16F</figureCitation>
) entirely dark brown.
</paragraph>
<caption id="F711B3F4C4C374293835ED5966DFBDA5" doi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" start="Figure 16" startId="F16">
<paragraph id="7FA36679AA986EA82D4F44ED4D60A5F1" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="41DC7EEBDCF8D7964FAE5DCF2DB7FA1E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Figure 16.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="ED25C8234510BF137CCED9245B02C213" authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys joanae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="joanae">
