</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="7FB11551B2BB1D30D6D0F31B42A63289" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">sp. nov. A</emphasis>
, Male habitus, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="9578A21BD55BA35F10D60EA07A3BE0B2" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">B</emphasis>
, Male habitus, ventral view; 
<emphasis id="3520409D65BB6111FDD6B9E2A9EC1BE2" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C</emphasis>
, Male antenna, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="93F2D6B9FA0D43205D50652A67761A7F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">D</emphasis>
, Male pronotum, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="88892096E0B80D10418EECEF5607A300" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">E</emphasis>
, Sternum IX, ventral view; 
<emphasis id="2BD600277848AB6A110EE6750EC1B93E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">F</emphasis>
, Pygidium, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="DD53D0505A5811EB1DFA8C5C313BEF0A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">G</emphasis>
, Syntergite, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="C4BD35B9B299BE3210130CF03435114E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">H</emphasis>
, Sternum IX, Ventral view; 
<emphasis id="31BC50B96B33A2D6C7B2B932A2F30A40" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">I</emphasis>
, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; 
<emphasis id="084D84E4F024120AD2BAB8C5CFF39878" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">J</emphasis>
, Aedeagus, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="BEEB441D2B663A4406A4744DA9E6E9EB" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">K</emphasis>
, Aedeagus, ventral view; 
<emphasis id="51B56C4903F0EA825506DCE94C2F411A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">L</emphasis>
, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="F41BCFF819E89F237A3314CD184789FD" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="38CE739BB2884B7BB7D9C233A1C72B7B" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16D</figureCitation>
) with sides rounded, divergent posteriorly. 
<emphasis id="DDF3E229C6A7EF8767BF831C7AFE7165" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Male.</emphasis>
Total length = 10.6 mm; Pronotal length = 2.2 mm; Pronotal width = 3.6 mm; Elytral length = 8.4 mm; Elytral width = 2.3 mm. Antennomere III (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="69E5BD4CEED1CC73D5068D97FC52A25E" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16C</figureCitation>
) with lamella about 4
<normalizedToken id="A520F73B9D4CCDA507E977594C5CD253" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than core antennomere. Sternum VI (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4AFC56687865F5D2748A859074D63416" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16B</figureCitation>
) with a small lantern, occupying the medial 1/6 of the sternum, not reaching its anterior margin. Sternum VIII (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3B24AF1E472D10C1474EF661CEC097C3" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16E</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin bisinuose. Pygidium (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3E3EB921475A4D4BEC09AB9496C4C7C7" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16F</figureCitation>
) with sides rounded and abruptly converging posteriorly from basal third on, posterior corners barely visible, posterior margin rounded, somewhat acuminate. Syntergite (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B09B0E7A1BE109C9A7415999817216DE" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16G,H</figureCitation>
) boomerang-shaped (with anterior margin strongly curved). Phallus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="80FFA494659D1B247392A46FFE1CC05D" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Costalampys joanae sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Sternum IX, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view, blue arrow pointing to the transverse keel on the dorsal plate; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view; L, Aedeagus, oblique view, red arrow pointing to the ventral plate. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (D-L)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543219" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">16I-L</figureCitation>
) with dorsal plate curved dorsally in lateral view, with sides rounded at apical half, slightly convergent apically. Paramere apex almost straight, ventral projection (lateral view) moderately developed, almost right-angled. 
<emphasis id="DFFB2DA477BB681BFDFE976922DF603F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="64A7F5538E4C61014C730E9C41DBC917" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="E4E406BCA401E095AEDC67A2C3B7A532" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="05CA5313D47B2DE6856A0CB677EEEF61" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName id="A153CAC94AE7329FBC832CF55B7A9461" authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys joanae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="joanae">
<emphasis id="D6E4619DD09F2A6758F3125567919751" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys joanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="63511792F2DA858C987CA09DC0A8DDE1" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">sp. nov.</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="693AF7258302C0C5E7471FDCC4B2A209" genus="C." lsidName="C. delicata" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="delicata">
<emphasis id="A2F7745FF54B6A452FB67DF4A69EA1F9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. delicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="D313C7E3395612EEF7E1EB37943BC6CD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">sp. nov.</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F9F792EBFB80CA9AA591DE2004005C1E" genus="C." lsidName="C. decorata" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="decorata">
<emphasis id="63BAFA3535A743FFC2D2B3A4116CA3B3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. decorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Olivier, 1888) 
<emphasis id="CEBBE9DC028AED2CB37353999536B792" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2BC588E122955181E49EC39833F808EA" genus="C." lsidName="C. tricolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis id="ACC893D1894C35FF6D187920DAD6A419" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Gorham, 1880) 
<emphasis id="37C638E43CB658EC32EE5C548010A456" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="18D79E2B83200F3EC1D8E18F790CAFCF" genus="C." lsidName="C. bella" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis id="F5E63AAA3791AC78A0C202134173AEF0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="46760739C55B83F337D55F3D9D2DCEED" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">sp. nov.</emphasis>
, in the dorsal color pattern (overall brown or dark brown, with pronotal disc broadly pink, and with an elongate pale-yellow spot on elytron). 
<taxonomicName id="0CBB66506BDB9AC6461AABBE61B91A35" authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys joanae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="joanae">
<emphasis id="4F18E5A64B5097B78EA0D083CE4709AF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys joanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="488115A19A771DEBCE2FA6C0171A5159" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">sp. nov.</emphasis>
is unique among the aforementioned species by having a longer antennomere III lamella, which is about 4
<normalizedToken id="D6FEC175718A7B0E9AACFC479DD5761C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than core antennomere, as well as sides of pygidium strongly convergent posteriorly (homogeneously rounded in the other species).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="53C5B626B8F05CAA8E99F93C3C599F23" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FA5564AE57A94964D0FC9719CA991660" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Etymology.</paragraph>
